title: Unable to "import deeplabcut"
body:
**Operating system and DeepLabCut version**

OS: Ubuntu18.04 with Anaconda Env
DeepLabCut Version: gitclone latest master (unable to check directly, couldn't import)
Browser: Chrome
Using JupyterNotebook

**Problem**

Tried to use the Demo Notebook after installation, unable to perform first step - "import deeplabcut"

**Steps to Reproduce the problem**

1. git clone https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut.git 
2. "cd" into, the folder named conda-environments
3. conda env create -f dlc-ubuntu-GPU.yaml
4. source activate dlc-ubuntu-GPU , command terminal has changed with the correct environment name 
5. conda install nb_conda
6. open new notebook  or one of the demonotebooks, and try "import deeplabcut"
7. See error

**Error Trace:**
    
    ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
     ModuleNotFoundError                       Traceback (most recent call last)
     <ipython-input-4-cfa4f159dfc5> in <module>
     ----> 1 import deeplabcut

    ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'deeplabcut'

**Screenshots**

If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.
![Screenshot from 2019-08-21 11-12-28](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/39631487/63456812-9d54bb80-c404-11e9-9add-77db95137a76.png)


**Additional context**

Tried  installing later with  "pip install deeplabcut" as an added second measure, but it failed with this error:

       |████████████████████████████████| 256kB 34.2MB/s

         cwd: /tmp/pip-install-uztvsd6k/ruamel.yaml/
    Complete output (26 lines):
